Text.LocalizedString: Great weather. Great weather, indeed.

Text.SourceString: That’s why I’m out here, <PlayerName>$player</>. Why else?
Text.LocalizedString: That’s why I’m out here, <PlayerName>$player</>. Why else?

Text.SourceString: Psst…
Text.LocalizedString: Psst…

Text.SourceString: I’m trying to capture footage. Will you keep your voice down, please?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m trying to capture footage. Will you keep your voice down, please?

Text.SourceString: I’m at the lake a lot. It’s my job.//Gotta go where my job takes me. Seems like you are too, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m at the lake a lot. It’s my job.//Gotta go where my job takes me. Seems like you are too, huh?

Text.SourceString: What are you doing here this time of day, anyway?
Text.LocalizedString: What are you doing here this time of day, anyway?

Text.SourceString: I saw a couple of monkeys taking a bath in the lake the other day. It’s pretty hard to predict when they’ll be out.
Text.LocalizedString: I saw a couple of monkeys taking a bath in the lake the other day. It’s pretty hard to predict when they’ll be out.

Text.SourceString: I don’t want to get too close to them. It’s their home. I don’t want to intrude.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t want to get too close to them. It’s their home. I don’t want to intrude.

Text.SourceString: Uh… I don’t know who comes here on weekends. I usually spend mine at the beach.
Text.LocalizedString: Uh… I don’t know who comes here on weekends. I usually spend mine at the beach.

Text.SourceString: But I’m here pretty much throughout the week, if that means anything.
Text.LocalizedString: But I’m here pretty much throughout the week, if that means anything.

Text.SourceString: I just finished editing last week’s footage. Everything is coming along great! Now onto the fun stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: I just finished editing last week’s footage. Everything is coming along great! Now onto the fun stuff.

Text.SourceString: Well, yeah. My wife does most of the editing. She likes it.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, yeah. My wife does most of the editing. She likes it.

Text.SourceString: It’s tough to get footage of the corpse flower. The plant doesn’t flower often.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s tough to get footage of the corpse flower. The plant doesn’t flower often.

Text.SourceString: I know it’s technically a plant, but it’s rare, huh? People love to see it. We certainly do.
Text.LocalizedString: I know it’s technically a plant, but it’s rare, huh? People love to see it. We certainly do.

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>! Great to see you, my friend.//Are you here to see the animal footage we got yesterday?
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>! Great to see you, my friend.//Are you here to see the animal footage we got yesterday?

Text.SourceString: <Italic>Hey!</> <NPCName>Anne</>! We have a guest!
Text.LocalizedString: <Italic>Hey!</> <NPCName>Anne</>! We have a guest!

Text.SourceString: I don’t see you here very often, <PlayerName>$player</>. I hope things are okay back at the farm.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t see you here very often, <PlayerName>$player</>. I hope things are okay back at the farm.

Text.SourceString: I was looking at a space back there to put a small pet house, maybe. Not for a pet, but shelter for wild animals.
Text.LocalizedString: I was looking at a space back there to put a small pet house, maybe. Not for a pet, but shelter for wild animals.

Text.SourceString: Some of the bulbs on our porch burned out. Be careful going home, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: Some of the bulbs on our porch burned out. Be careful going home, okay?

Text.SourceString: I haven’t had time to change them. We don’t get visitors often anyway.//Besides, wildlife doesn’t like a lot of light at night.
Text.LocalizedString: I haven’t had time to change them. We don’t get visitors often anyway.//Besides, wildlife doesn’t like a lot of light at night.

Text.SourceString: Sweating the day away, <PlayerName>$player</>? I’m playing volleyball with the family.//<portrait=happy>Trying to see if I can still beat my wife at it.
Text.LocalizedString: Sweating the day away, <PlayerName>$player</>? I’m playing volleyball with the family.//<portrait=happy>Trying to see if I can still beat my wife at it.

Text.SourceString: Come on, <NPCName>Zoe</>! Let’s see who the winners are!
Text.LocalizedString: Come on, <NPCName>Zoe</>! Let’s see who the winners are!

Text.SourceString: You can always dive into the ocean if it gets too hot.//Cool down a bit, eh? Don’t overheat!
Text.LocalizedString: You can always dive into the ocean if it gets too hot.//Cool down a bit, eh? Don’t overheat!

Text.SourceString: Keep your hat handy!
Text.LocalizedString: Keep your hat handy!

Text.SourceString: We get to see seals and all kinds of fish here. Turtles come to the shore sometimes, but not very often.//So keep an eye out.
Text.LocalizedString: We get to see seals and all kinds of fish here. Turtles come to the shore sometimes, but not very often.//So keep an eye out.

Text.SourceString: A couple of <NPCName>Zoe’s</> friends live around here. She always has a lot of fun at the beach.
Text.LocalizedString: A couple of <NPCName>Zoe’s</> friends live around here. She always has a lot of fun at the beach.

Text.SourceString: Oh, ho, ho, ho! <PlayerName>$player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, ho, ho, ho! <PlayerName>$player</>!

Text.SourceString: Did you say something? Really?//Ah, must be the music. It’s so loud, I can hardly make anything out. Apologies!
Text.LocalizedString: Did you say something? Really?//Ah, must be the music. It’s so loud, I can hardly make anything out. Apologies!

Text.SourceString: And then the bear was behind me all along! That was scary. Very, very scary. The forest can be scary at times.//But of course, I had to keep calm. <NPCName>Anne</> was with me. Didn’t want to spook the bear.//We stayed inside the tent the whole night.
Text.LocalizedString: And then the bear was behind me all along! That was scary. Very, very scary. The forest can be scary at times.//But of course, I had to keep calm. <NPCName>Anne</> was with me. Didn’t want to spook the bear.//We stayed inside the tent the whole night.

Text.SourceString: What in the world is this song? Do you think <NPCName>Theo</> wrote it himself?
Text.LocalizedString: What in the world is this song? Do you think <NPCName>Theo</> wrote it himself?

Text.SourceString: It’s certainly one of a kind! Let’s dance to it!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s certainly one of a kind! Let’s dance to it!

Text.SourceString: I always love visits from <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</>. What personalities they have.
Text.LocalizedString: I always love visits from <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</>. What personalities they have.

Text.SourceString: Oh, they’re <NPCName>Erika’s</> cats. For some reason, they always come around late at night.//I wonder if she knows about it.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, they’re <NPCName>Erika’s</> cats. For some reason, they always come around late at night.//I wonder if she knows about it.

Text.SourceString: There’s lots of ways you can help the environment! Building bee hotels, for instance.//<NPCName>Ben</> has some near his cara…errr…house.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s lots of ways you can help the environment! Building bee hotels, for instance.//<NPCName>Ben</> has some near his cara…errr…house.

Text.SourceString: A simple thing like refilling bird feeders can help wildlife, and it takes less than ten minutes.//<portrait=happy>Everybody has ten minutes in their week, eh?
Text.LocalizedString: A simple thing like refilling bird feeders can help wildlife, and it takes less than ten minutes.//<portrait=happy>Everybody has ten minutes in their week, eh?

Text.SourceString: I spend a lot of time in the wild.//While we have a good environment for the animals here, I know many islands still need help.
Text.LocalizedString: I spend a lot of time in the wild.//While we have a good environment for the animals here, I know many islands still need help.

Text.SourceString: I can’t wear bright, colorful things. I need to keep a low profile.//Don’t wanna spook the animals, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t wear bright, colorful things. I need to keep a low profile.//Don’t wanna spook the animals, you know?

Text.SourceString: But hey, you can wear whatever you want!//It seems like you’re already doing just that. Good on you, mate!
Text.LocalizedString: But hey, you can wear whatever you want!//It seems like you’re already doing just that. Good on you, mate!

Text.SourceString: I passed by your farm the other day on my way to the lookout.//<portrait=happy>Whoa! Good job you’re doing over there!
Text.LocalizedString: I passed by your farm the other day on my way to the lookout.//<portrait=happy>Whoa! Good job you’re doing over there!

Text.SourceString: Taking care of such a large property takes not just skill but dedication.//Hats off, my friend!
Text.LocalizedString: Taking care of such a large property takes not just skill but dedication.//Hats off, my friend!

Text.SourceString: Ha ha ha! Wrong person, <PlayerName>$player</>. Not <NPCName>Walter</>.//<portrait=normal>I’m still <NPCName>Paul</>!
Text.LocalizedString: Ha ha ha! Wrong person, <PlayerName>$player</>. Not <NPCName>Walter</>.//<portrait=normal>I’m still <NPCName>Paul</>!

Text.SourceString: Somebody had too much fun this weekend. Heh heh.
Text.LocalizedString: Somebody had too much fun this weekend. Heh heh.

Text.SourceString: <Italic>Oh my!</>//What do you have there?
Text.LocalizedString: <Italic>Oh my!</>//What do you have there?

Text.SourceString: Ah, they’re just your hands. Sorry. Didn’t mean to alarm you.//<portrait=normal>I thought you were carrying… Never mind.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, they’re just your hands. Sorry. Didn’t mean to alarm you.//<portrait=normal>I thought you were carrying… Never mind.

Text.SourceString: Parrots are brilliant. And very social, a lot like us.
Text.LocalizedString: Parrots are brilliant. And very social, a lot like us.

Text.SourceString: I feel so alive today. The river is flowing, the air is crisp.//The birds! Oh, the birds are chirping.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel so alive today. The river is flowing, the air is crisp.//The birds! Oh, the birds are chirping.

Text.SourceString: Sunshine dayyyyy~ Sunshineeeee awakeeeees~ Oh, my sunshinyyyyy dayyyyy~
Text.LocalizedString: Sunshine dayyyyy~ Sunshineeeee awakeeeees~ Oh, my sunshinyyyyy dayyyyy~

Text.SourceString: I’ve only seen a white crocodile once in my life. He was big. He had a name…something something.//I can’t remember it for the life of me.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve only seen a white crocodile once in my life. He was big. He had a name…something something.//I can’t remember it for the life of me.

Text.SourceString: Oh, um… I believe that particular one was an albino crocodile.//Very rare, you know. If I had to put a number on it, I’d say there’s maybe only 100 of them in the world.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, um… I believe that particular one was an albino crocodile.//Very rare, you know. If I had to put a number on it, I’d say there’s maybe only 100 of them in the world.

Text.SourceString: I used to wear hiking boots everywhere, and it was fine.//But then, as soon as I tried <Italic>this</> kind of boots – oh boy!//That was it.
Text.LocalizedString: I used to wear hiking boots everywhere, and it was fine.//But then, as soon as I tried <Italic>this</> kind of boots – oh boy!//That was it.

Text.SourceString: After two days of working in these boots, they were my favorite pair.//Wanna try them on?
Text.LocalizedString: After two days of working in these boots, they were my favorite pair.//Wanna try them on?

Text.SourceString: What kind of boots do you wear? You and me – we’re the same, you know?//Both on our feet all day, every day.
Text.LocalizedString: What kind of boots do you wear? You and me – we’re the same, you know?//Both on our feet all day, every day.

Text.SourceString: I wear only hiking boots now. My feet get really hot after working for a while, but these… They have a nice cooling effect.
Text.LocalizedString: I wear only hiking boots now. My feet get really hot after working for a while, but these… They have a nice cooling effect.

Text.SourceString: I was in a band back in university, you know.//Maybe not as talented as <NPCName>Theo</>, but I had my day.
Text.LocalizedString: I was in a band back in university, you know.//Maybe not as talented as <NPCName>Theo</>, but I had my day.

Text.SourceString: My wife here will tell you the same thing. Ask away!//<portrait=normal>In fact, I think I still have some old pictures somewhere at the house.
Text.LocalizedString: My wife here will tell you the same thing. Ask away!//<portrait=normal>In fact, I think I still have some old pictures somewhere at the house.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Anne</> has been grilling fish lately.//We got a deal from <NPCName>Sunny</>, so she bought a lot on the weekend.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Anne</> has been grilling fish lately.//We got a deal from <NPCName>Sunny</>, so she bought a lot on the weekend.

Text.SourceString: I don’t think I can eat any more fish tonight.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think I can eat any more fish tonight.

Text.SourceString: We grow some crops in our garden. It’s a good way for <NPCName>Zoe</> to bond with nature.//We planted some corn, melons. What else did we plant?
Text.LocalizedString: We grow some crops in our garden. It’s a good way for <NPCName>Zoe</> to bond with nature.//We planted some corn, melons. What else did we plant?

Text.SourceString: I wouldn’t mind if the animals ate our corn.//Sharing is caring, eh?
Text.LocalizedString: I wouldn’t mind if the animals ate our corn.//Sharing is caring, eh?

Text.SourceString: I’m saving some money to put toward a wildlife conservation fund.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m saving some money to put toward a wildlife conservation fund.

Text.SourceString: I do what I can, but I want to do more. Build large wildlife conservation areas on secluded islands, help the locals, educate our youth.
Text.LocalizedString: I do what I can, but I want to do more. Build large wildlife conservation areas on secluded islands, help the locals, educate our youth.

Text.SourceString: I was in a band back in university, ya know.//Maybe not as talented as <NPCName>Theo</>, but I had my day.
Text.LocalizedString: I was in a band back in university, ya know.//Maybe not as talented as <NPCName>Theo</>, but I had my day.

Text.SourceString: My wife here will tell you the same thing. Ask away!//<portrait=normal>In fact, I think I still have some old pictures somewhere at the house.
Text.LocalizedString: My wife here will tell you the same thing. Ask away!//<portrait=normal>In fact, I think I still have some old pictures somewhere at the house.

Text.SourceString: Music here sure is banging!
Text.LocalizedString: Music here sure is banging!

Text.SourceString: Retiring my vest for a bit.//It can’t take the snow…too thin.
Text.LocalizedString: Retiring my vest for a bit.//It can’t take the snow…too thin.

Text.SourceString: We forgot to clear the garden before Winter. Now we have frozen crops in our garden.//I think we’ll just wait for Spring to clean it up. No point in doing it right now, eh?
Text.LocalizedString: We forgot to clear the garden before Winter. Now we have frozen crops in our garden.//I think we’ll just wait for Spring to clean it up. No point in doing it right now, eh?

Text.SourceString: We forgot to clear the garden before Winter. So, for a long time, we had frozen crops in our garden.//Good thing it wasn’t hard to clear it up. Frozen and all.
Text.LocalizedString: We forgot to clear the garden before Winter. So, for a long time, we had frozen crops in our garden.//Good thing it wasn’t hard to clear it up. Frozen and all.

Text.SourceString: We started planting carrots and potatoes already.
Text.LocalizedString: We started planting carrots and potatoes already.

Text.SourceString: Ah, my vest! I miss it.//It smells kind of musty, but I’m sure it’ll be better after it airs out some.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, my vest! I miss it.//It smells kind of musty, but I’m sure it’ll be better after it airs out some.

Text.SourceString: Damg, every time I see <NpcName>Theo</>'s boat at the beach I get major boat envy. It's so sick!//<portrait=normal>I wonder if he'd let me borrow it for a day.
Text.LocalizedString: Damg, every time I see <NpcName>Theo</>'s boat at the beach I get major boat envy. It's so sick!//<portrait=normal>I wonder if he'd let me borrow it for a day.

Text.SourceString: I've been itching to take the family out on the water for ages. <NpcName>Theo</>'s boat would be perfect, but I don't wanna be all up in his business, ya know?//<portrait=annoyed>Maybe I'll just casually mention I wanna go fishing and see if he offers to let me use it.
Text.LocalizedString: I've been itching to take the family out on the water for ages. <NpcName>Theo</>'s boat would be perfect, but I don't wanna be all up in his business, ya know?//<portrait=annoyed>Maybe I'll just casually mention I wanna go fishing and see if he offers to let me use it.
